{"questionId":"27750","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The region enclosed by the curve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis is rotated through&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math> radians about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis to form a solid of revolution.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider a function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Find the value of</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use the chain rule &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>